SIMPLE: fighting
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fighting
<hw>Fight"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Qualified for war;
fit for battle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An host of <qex>fighting</qex> men.</q> <rj><qau>2 Chron. xxvi.
11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Occupied in war; being the scene of a battle;
<as>as, a <ex>fighting</ex> field</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>A fighting chance</b></col>, <cd>one dependent upon the
issue of a struggle.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> -- <col><b>Fighting
crab</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the fiddler crab.</cd> --
<col><b>Fighting fish</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a remarkably
pugnacious East Indian fish (<spn>Betta pugnax</spn>), reared by the
Siamese for spectacular fish fights.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fightingly</ent>⟦br⟧
